                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13771134" author="danrevel@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 18 Sep 2013 19:22:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Consumer should not send basicAck on channels that are doing autoAck.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13782765" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 09:47:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13791378" author="fergusn" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 10:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the patch is broken. The logic is wrong. From the comment above from Dan - &quot;Consumer should not send basicAck on channels that are doing autoAck.&quot; the logic below is missing the not. Needs a ! added to the if.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+                if (consumer.endpoint.isAutoAck()) {&lt;br/&gt;
+                    log.trace(&quot;Acknowledging receipt &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;delivery_tag={}&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;, deliveryTag);&lt;br/&gt;
+                    channel.basicAck(deliveryTag, false);&lt;br/&gt;
+                }&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13791444" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 12:39:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah it seems to make sense to only ack if auto ack is disabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13791457" author="fergusn" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 12:59:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pull request - &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/48&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/48&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13791477" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 13:29:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
